bug.author: soliverr
bug.summary: WebUI browse don't display files under table partition
bug.description:
Alluxio Version: 2.0.0 Describe the bug I have created partitioned table in Spark-SQL connected to Alluxio storage (/db directory in my environment). Her is list of files from Alluxio CLI (test_table has two partitioned columns): <denchmark-code>$ALLUXIO_HOME/bin/alluxio fs ls --sort lastModificationTime /db/test_table/VERSION_ID=3958/ drwxr-xr-x hadoop hadoop 1 NOT_PERSISTED 09-03-2019 18:32:10:687 DIR /db/test_table/VERSION_ID=3958/SCN=1 drwxr-xr-x hadoop hadoop 1 NOT_PERSISTED 09-04-2019 12:50:40:439 DIR /db/test_table/VERSION_ID=3958/SCN=2 </denchmark-code>
But in WebUI Browse nothing displayed when I click /db/test_table/VERSION_ID=3958 link. To Reproduce Create partitioned table in Spark-SQL. Take a look into WebUI Browse. Expected behavior In Alluxio 1.8.1 WebUi Browse all contents was displayed correctly.

comments.comment: <denchmark-link:https://github.com/tieujason330>@tieujason330</denchmark-link> Is this something that was fixed in 2.0.1? It sounds like the characters in the URL might not have been encoded properly.

<denchmark-link:https://github.com/ZacBlanco>@ZacBlanco</denchmark-link> Yeah it's in 2.0.1. It's a very similar issue to <denchmark-link:https://github.com/Alluxio/alluxio/issues/9465>#9465</denchmark-link> that was fixed a couple months back.
<denchmark-link:https://github.com/soliverr>@soliverr</denchmark-link> Can you upgrade to 2.0.1 and try? We've fixed a number of issues in the latest patch release.
Thank you. I've missed this update. Now it's working well in 2.0.1.
